While working on this task, I gained practical experience using both coding and collaboration platforms. Creating an account on HackerRank and solving a beginner-level problem helped me understand how coding platforms work and how problems are structured. It was interesting to see how even simple problems require logical thinking and proper understanding.

I also created a Google Form for a digital literacy quiz, which helped me learn how to design questions and collect responses efficiently. Viewing responses in Google Sheets was a new experience, and it showed me how data can be organized and analyzed easily.

One challenge I faced was understanding the coding platform interface at first, but after exploring it, I became more comfortable. Overall, this task helped me improve my problem-solving skills and introduced me to useful tools that will support my academic learning and collaboration in the future.
